In its Mine 2019: Resourcing the future report, the multi-national professional services network states that, as a group, the top fourty mining firms increased revenue by 8% to $683 billion, buoyed by higher commodity prices and a 2% growth in production.  

However, investors seem unimpressed by the Top 40's result, judging by market valuations, which fell 18% over 2018. More from Sheivaan Naidoo, PwC Senior Manager… --Channelafrica--